(146, 209, 'olidev', 'oliverusselldev@gmail.com', '', '202.69.48.90', '2017-02-28 12:32:34', '2017-02-28 07:02:34', 'This is a nice guide for install LAMP stack with PHP 5 on AWS EC2. Since PHP 7 is out now, you should update this guide. Also, it is now much easier to install PHP on AWS because of PaaS solutions we have now. Here is an example of how you can use a PaaS to install PHP on AWS: https://www.cloudways.com/blog/host-php-on-aws-cloud/ \r\nThe difference is that you don\'t have spend time and effort on server management or system administration. You can solely focus on building your app.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/55.0.2883.87 Safari/537.36', '', 0, 0),
