(148, 209, 'Intuz', 'intuzhq@gmail.com', 'https://cloud.intuz.com/applications', '103.50.152.122', '2017-04-24 17:03:25', '2017-04-24 11:33:25', 'For hosting LAMP on AWS you do not need to learn all the technical stuffs, you can host LAMP on AWS using one click ready-to-run LAMP AMI (Amazon Machine Image).\r\n\r\nTo launch this stack on Amazon EC2 you need to follow the steps below:\r\n\r\nStep 1: Once the instance is running, enter the public IP provided by Amazon into your browser.\r\n\r\nStep 2: Wait for the instance health checks to pass. You will then see the apache default page. \r\n\r\nStep 3: You can access \'/phpmyadmin\' page and use \'root\' as username and \'instance-id\' as password. \r\n\r\nStep 4: You can access \'webmin\' admin page at port 8000 and use \'admin\' as username and \'instance-id\' as password.. You may change this username and password within the application settings.\r\n\r\nStep 5: You can also access your instance via SSH using the username \'ubuntu\' and your Amazon private key. \r\n\r\nFor additional setup instructions to run scripts and ftp please visit to: http://cloud.intuz.com/applications/lamp-stack/aws/how-to-use\r\nhttps://aws.amazon.com/marketplace/pp/B01N6Z1NL2/?ref_=_ptnr_intuz_ami_lamp-stack', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/57.0.2987.133 Safari/537.36', '', 0, 0),
