(24, 1, '2016-12-02 11:13:36', '2016-12-02 11:13:36', 'Whenever we install wordpress on Amazon(EC2) instance then its necessary to set the file permissions as below:\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\"><code><span class=\"pln\">chown www</span><span class=\"pun\">-</span><span class=\"pln\">data</span><span class=\"pun\">:</span><span class=\"pln\">www</span><span class=\"pun\">-</span><span class=\"pln\">data  </span><span class=\"pun\">-</span><span class=\"pln\">R </span><span class=\"pun\">*</span> <span class=\"com\"># Let Apache be owner</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\nfind </span><span class=\"pun\">.</span> <span class=\"pun\">-</span><span class=\"pln\">type d </span><span class=\"pun\">-</span><span class=\"kwd\">exec</span><span class=\"pln\"> chmod </span><span class=\"lit\">755</span> <span class=\"pun\">{}</span><span class=\"pln\"> \\;  </span><span class=\"com\"># Change directory permissions rwxr-xr-x</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\nfind </span><span class=\"pun\">.</span> <span class=\"pun\">-</span><span class=\"pln\">type f </span><span class=\"pun\">-</span><span class=\"kwd\">exec</span><span class=\"pln\"> chmod </span><span class=\"lit\">644</span> <span class=\"pun\">{}</span><span class=\"pln\"> \\;  </span><span class=\"com\"># Change file permissions rw-r--r--</span></code></pre>\r\nAfter applying these permission you don\'t need to set the permission for wp-content folder. Admin will be able to add media in wordpress.\r\n\r\nFor more security please read <a href=\"http://codex.wordpress.org/Hardening_WordPress\">Hardening WordPress</a>', 'Set File Permissions for WordPress on Amazon EC2', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'set-file-permissions-for-wordpress-on-amazon-ec2', '', '', '2016-12-02 12:01:48', '2016-12-02 12:01:48', '', 0, 'http://trickntip.com/?p=24', 0, 'post', '', 1),
