(123, 1, '2016-12-12 09:49:59', '2016-12-12 09:49:59', 'The Best Way To Make Sticky Footers using CSS and HTML5 is explained here. HTML5 has many tags that you can use to reduce the code. Here, I will explain in the details that how you can use HTML5 and CSS to do this without any breakdown in all devices.\r\n\r\nFirst of all, lets see the HTML markup:\r\n<pre>&lt;body&gt; \r\n    &lt;header&gt;Add Header Elements&lt;/header&gt; \r\n    &lt;section class=\"main-content\"&gt;Add Body Content and Elements&lt;/section&gt; \r\n    &lt;footer&gt;Add Footer Elements&lt;/footer&gt; \r\n&lt;/body&gt;</pre>\r\nNow lets see the CSS part:\r\n<pre> html{ \r\n    height: 100%; \r\n} \r\n \r\nbody{ \r\n    display: flex; \r\n    flex-direction: column; \r\n    height: 100%; \r\n} \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\nheader{ \r\n   /* header to have a static height,  it will always take up just as much space as it needs.  */ \r\n   /* 0 flex-grow, 0 flex-shrink, auto flex-basis */ \r\n   flex: 0 0 auto; \r\n} \r\n \r\n.main-content{ \r\n   /*flex-grow to 1 by setting, the main content will take up all of the remaining space on the page.  \r\n   The other elements have flex-grow: 0 and won\'t contest the free space. */ \r\n   /* 1 flex-grow, 0 flex-shrink, auto flex-basis */ \r\n   flex: 1 0 auto; \r\n} \r\n \r\nfooter{ \r\n   /* Like header, the footer will have a static height - it should not grow or shrink.  */ \r\n   /* 0 flex-grow, 0 flex-shrink, auto flex-basis */ \r\n   flex: 0 0 auto; \r\n}</pre>\r\nIn CSS3 \'flex\' property is introduced to automatically accommodate the size according to device. All latest web browsers support this property.\r\n\r\nThats it!', 'Best Way To Make Sticky Footers Using CSS and HTML5', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'best-way-make-sticky-footers-using-css-html5', '', '', '2016-12-12 10:10:31', '2016-12-12 10:10:31', '', 0, 'http://trickntip.com/?p=123', 0, 'post', '', 2),
