(130, 1, '2016-12-13 09:36:04', '2016-12-13 09:36:04', 'Ionic can handle the splash screens automatically. There are few steps to add the splash screen and app icon to your iOS and Android App.\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Place two initial files in your project/resources directory:\r\nicon.png\r\nsplash.png</li>\r\n 	<li>Make sure that sizes are correct\r\nicon.png (192 x 192)\r\nsplash.png (2732 x 2732)</li>\r\n 	<li>Run the following command:</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<pre>$ ionic resources\r\nOr individually run for both one by one\r\n$ ionic resources --splash\r\n$ ionic resources --icon\r\n</pre>\r\nAfter doing this, if your splash screen does not display, then you need to delete your specific platform. For example, if your\r\nare working on iOS then you need to remove iOS platform and then again add iOS platform again and follow the above three steps again. Please see the commands to add/remove platform in Ionic.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n $ ionic platform remove ios\r\n $ ionic platform add ios\r\n</pre>', 'Splash Screen Not Displaying On Ionic iOS App', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'splash-screen-not-displaying-ionic-ios-app', '', '', '2016-12-13 09:36:04', '2016-12-13 09:36:04', '', 0, 'http://trickntip.com/?p=130', 0, 'post', '', 0),
