(151, 1, '2016-12-21 05:34:32', '2016-12-21 05:34:32', 'There are many times when you need to configure the phpmyadmin so that you can have better UI to manage databases and SQL operations. In this article, you will know that how you can install phpmyadmin in ubuntu 16.04 LAMP. Before we go with the steps, we assume that you are having good knowledge about the CLI(Command Line Interface) in ubuntu.\r\n\r\nStep 1: Install phpmyadmin using the following command\r\n<pre> apt-get install phpmyadmin</pre>\r\nStep 2: The installer will ask you an option to use dbconfig-common to configure phpMyAdmin. Please select \'Yes\' option\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-149 size-large\" src=\"http://trickntip.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Configure-Phpmyadmin-1024x188.jpg\" alt=\"configure-phpmyadmin\" width=\"840\" height=\"154\" />\r\n\r\nStep 3: Set password for the phpmyadmin.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-150\" src=\"http://trickntip.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Define-phpmyadmin-database-password-1024x171.jpg\" alt=\"define-phpmyadmin-database-password\" width=\"840\" height=\"140\" />\r\n\r\nyou will asked again to confirm the password\r\n\r\nStep 4: Once finished with the password, phpMyAdmin should now been installed successfully.\r\n\r\nStep 5: There are many PHP modules that you need to install so that your phpmyadmin can work. Please run the following command:\r\n<pre> apt-get install php-mbstring php7.0-mbstring php-gettext</pre>\r\nStep 6: Your phpMyAdmin is installed now, but its not accessible by default. You need to adjust Apache2 config file to make phpMyAdmin accessible:\r\n<pre> nano /etc/apache2/apache2.conf</pre>\r\nStep 7: Scroll down the configuration page till the bottom and add the following line.\r\n<pre> Include /etc/phpmyadmin/apache.conf</pre>\r\nStep 8: Now you need to restart Apache2 service.\r\n<pre> service apache2 restart</pre>\r\n\r\nCongratulations! Now you can access phpmyadmin using your domain or IP http://x.x.x.x/phpmyadmin\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'Install phpmyadmin in Ubuntu 16.04', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '148-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-12-21 05:34:32', '2016-12-21 05:34:32', '', 148, 'http://trickntip.com/148-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
