(209, 1, '2017-01-01 05:56:36', '2017-01-01 05:56:36', 'Amazon has its best services and products. EC2(Elastic Compute Cloud) is one out of them. In this article we will explain you that how To Install LAMP Stack on Ubuntu 14.04 on AWS EC2. Amazon provides one year free tire for their customers so that they can experience their services before purchase.\r\n<h2>Prerequisites</h2>\r\nWe assume that you already have created Amazon EC2 instance for Ubuntu 14.04 and SSH to run the commands along with .pem or .ppk file. You must have a basic knowledge about the Linux CLI(Command Line Interface). Please see below the steps to install LAMP(Linux, Apache, MySQL, PHP) on EC2.\r\n<h3>[showad block=3]</h3>\r\n<h3>1. Connect to your EC2 instance</h3>\r\nPlease connect to your EC2 instance using SSH. If you remember, you have downloaded the .pem file to connect to your EC2 instance. Right click on your instance and you will see \'Connect\' option. Just click it:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_210\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"812\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-210\" src=\"http://trickntip.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/amazon-instance-connect-option.png\" alt=\"How To Install LAMP Stack on Ubuntu 14.04 on AWS EC2\" width=\"812\" height=\"219\" /> How To Install LAMP Stack on Ubuntu 14.04 on AWS EC2[/caption]\r\n\r\nNow you will see a popup window to with the command example. Just copy the command and paste in your SSH. The command will look something like below:\r\n<pre>ssh -i \"yourfilename.pem\" ubuntu@ec2-32-144-3-135.ap-south-1.compute.amazonaws.com</pre>\r\n<h3>2. Update Operating System</h3>\r\nMake sure that your OS(Operating System) is up to date. Please run the following commands:\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<pre>sudo apt-get update\r\nsudo apt-get upgrade\r\n</pre>\r\n<h3>3. Install Apache</h3>\r\nApache work on Port 80. So make sure that your security settings are set to Port 80. Lets install Apache\r\n<pre>sudo apt-get install apache</pre>\r\n<h3>4. Install MySQL</h3>\r\nMySQL is for database that you need for your website/application.\r\n<pre>sudo apt-get install mysql-server php5-mysql</pre>\r\n<h3>5. Install PHP5</h3>\r\nFinally, install PHP5 and two other modules.\r\n<pre>sudo apt-get install php5 libapache2-mod-php5 php5-mcrypt</pre>\r\nNow you are done with LAMP. You can also install phpmyadmin for your database operations. phpmyadmin is optional:\r\n<pre>sudo apt-get install phpmyadmin</pre>\r\nBy only running the above command, your phpmyadmin will not work. You need to make few other changes too. Please see how to <a href=\"http://trickntip.com/install-phpmyadmin-ubuntu-16-04/\">Install phpmyadmin in Ubuntu 16.04</a>. Steps are similar for 14.04.\r\n\r\nNow if you go to your public IP then you will see the Apache2 Ubuntu Default page.\r\n<h2>Summery</h2>\r\nThat\'s it. Now you are ready to run PHP and SQL on EC2. You can also install other packages on your EC2 instance that you needed. You can also connect to your EC2 instance using the FileZilla so that you can easily perform CRUD(Create Read Update Delete) options on files. We hope that you will definitely like our post and send the comments for further assistance if you face any issue.\r\n\r\nThanks for reading and keep sharing!\r\n\r\n[showad block=3]', 'How To Install LAMP Stack on Ubuntu 14.04 on AWS EC2', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'install-lamp-stack-ubuntu-14-04-aws-ec2', '', '\nhttp://trickntip.com/install-phpmyadmin-ubuntu-16-04/', '2017-01-14 11:00:20', '2017-01-14 05:30:20', '', 0, 'http://trickntip.com/?p=209', 0, 'post', '', 7),
