(217, 1, '2017-01-07 13:08:27', '2017-01-07 07:38:27', 'All JavaScript programmers have different thoughts regarding type of errors in JavaScript. This is very important to understand the type of error when write program in JavaScript so that we can debug the error and implement the exception handling where needed or applicable. JavaScript error can be a disaster for your web page because it halts entire JavaScript execution. In this article, we will explain type of errors in JavaScript.\r\n<h2>Prerequisites</h2>\r\nBefore we dig into type of errors in JavaScript, we assume that you have a good knowledge about JavaScript programming and most important is Firebug console. In this article, we will show you errors in Firebug console which provides a great assistance to web developers. Mainly there are three type of errors in JavaScript:\r\n<h3>1. Syntax Errors</h3>\r\nAs name depicts, syntax errors are grammatical errors in language similar like C or Java. Since, JavaScript is an interpreted language, syntax errors can not be caught until script is loaded or you must have an advance JavaScript editor like Dream Viewer . They can also known as loading errors and shows the like number where error is encountered. Please see the following code with syntax error:\r\n\r\n[js lang=\"js\"]\r\nvar a = 10;\r\nif(a &lt;= 5){  \r\n  alert(\'Yes\');\r\n[/js]\r\n\r\nOutput:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_218\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"658\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-218\" src=\"http://trickntip.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Type-of-Errors-in-JavaScript-Syntax-Error.png\" alt=\"Type of Errors in JavaScript - Syntax Error\" width=\"658\" height=\"163\" /> Type of Errors in JavaScript - Syntax Error[/caption]\r\n\r\nSee, error is clear that we have missed the } to close \'if\' body.\r\n<h3>2. Run Time Errors</h3>\r\nThe second type of error is run time error. They usually occurs when your programing is running without any syntax error. Let\'s suppose you have called a function but you did not define this function. When JavaScript interpreter comes across this code and it can not understand. Please see the following example:\r\n\r\n[js]function sum(a,b){\r\n  return a+b;\r\n}\r\n\r\nvar a = 10;\r\nvar b = 20;\r\n\r\nalert(sum(a,b));\r\n\r\n//Now lets call subtract function which is not defined\r\nalert(subtract(b,a));\r\n[/js]\r\n\r\nOutput:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_219\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"658\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-219\" src=\"http://trickntip.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Type-of-Errors-in-JavaScript-Run-Time-Error.png\" alt=\"Type of Errors in JavaScript-Run Time Error\" width=\"658\" height=\"207\" /> Type of Errors in JavaScript-Run Time Error[/caption]\r\n\r\nOne thing to note here that if you run the example code you will see alert(30) because the sum() function is successfully executed but when subtract() is called then it shows \'ReferenceError: subtract is not defined\' and execution is halt.\r\n<h3>3. Logical Errors</h3>\r\nWe all are very much familiar with logical errors. These type of error are very difficult to find because interpreter can not show these errors in console or anywhere else. You have to debug your code line by line or it can be a night mare for your. Please see few logical errors:\r\n\r\n[js]\r\nvar i = 10;\r\nif (i=1) {  } //incorrect\r\n\r\nif(i == 1) {    } //correct\r\n[/js]\r\n\r\nAnother example is, lets assume that you wrote a program that expects JSON-formatted data to be returned from the server. But unknown to you, the owner of that application transfers data in XML format.\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\nWe all are programmer and during development we face these errors in our code. We know that if error will be encountered then our process will be halt and it can prone your application to errors. So we suggest that you must use exception handling to make your application near to prefect. We hope that this article will help you understanding type of errors in JavaScript.\r\n\r\nIf you like this article, please keep share with your friends!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Type of Errors in JavaScript', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'javascript-error-types', '', '', '2017-01-14 10:56:15', '2017-01-14 05:26:15', '', 0, 'http://trickntip.com/?p=217', 0, 'post', '', 1),
