on. When JavaScript interpreter comes across this code and it can not understand. Please see the following example:\r\n<pre>function sum(a,b){\r\n  return a+b;\r\n}\r\n\r\nvar a = 10;\r\nvar b = 20;\r\n\r\nalert(sum(a,b));\r\n\r\n//Now lets call subtract function which is not defined\r\nalert(subtract(b,a));\r\n</pre>\r\nOutput:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_219\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"658\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-219\" src=\"http://trickntip.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Type-of-Errors-in-JavaScript-Run-Time-Error.png\" alt=\"Type of Errors in JavaScript-Run Time Error\" width=\"658\" height=\"207\" /> Type of Errors in JavaScript-Run Time Error[/caption]\r\n\r\nOne thing to note here that if you run the example code you will see alert(30) because the sum() function is successfully executed but when subtract() is called then it shows \'ReferenceError: subtract is not defined\' and execution is halt.\r\n<h3>3. Logical Errors</h3>\r\nWe all are very much familiar with logical errors. These type of error are very difficult to find because interpreter can not show these errors in console or anywhere else. You have to debug your code line by line or it can be a night mare for your. Please see few logical errors:\r\n<pre>var i = 10;\r\nif (i=1) {  } //incorrect\r\n\r\nif(i == 1) {    } //correct\r\n</pre>\r\nAnother example is, lets assume that you wrote a program that expects JSON-formatted data to be returned from the server. But unknown to you, the owner of that application transfers data in XML format.\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\nWe all are programmer and during development we face these errors in our code. We know that if error will be encountered then our process will be halt and it can prone your application to errors. So we suggest that you must use exception handling to make your application near to prefect. We hope that this article will help you understanding type of errors in JavaScript.\r\n\r\nIf you like this article, please keep shat with your friends!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Type of Errors in JavaScript', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '217-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-01-07 13:08:27', '2017-01-07 07:38:27', '', 217, 'http://trickntip.com/217-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
