(301, 1, '2017-02-10 18:01:17', '2017-02-10 12:31:17', 'Last month, I have created a Python package(module) for one of my project and I really wanted to distribute it so that instead of forcing other developers to clone my repository, I want to make it installable using pip install command. Actually pip is a command that can be use to install any package from https://pypi.python.org website. Python provides online software repository known as PyPI(Python Package Index) which is absolutely free repository for packages. You can share Python package on PyPI using some standards. In this article, I will share my first wonderfull experiense to upload my own module on PyPI.\r\n<h2>Introduction to PyPI</h2>\r\nPyPI(Python Package Index) is free online repository to share Python packages. It has a huge list of Python software package and easy_install or pip are well aware of this. Anyone can frealessly install any package form PyPI using pip install command.\r\n<h2>Register on PyPI</h2>\r\nPyPI has some rules that you need to follow to upload your package. Actually there are two repositories one is <a href=\"http://pypi.python.org/pypi?%3Aaction=register_form\">PyPI Live</a> and other is <a href=\"http://testpypi.python.org/pypi?%3Aaction=register_form\">PyPI Test</a>. I must recomend that you should create an account on both of these websites. Now the point comes in the mind that why Python has created these two sites. Every package that we install using pip, is downloaded from the PyPI Live site and install in your local Python copy. But PyPI Test is only created to test your package submissions. You can not rely on PyPI Test because they regularly clean uploaded packages from the server. So, now you know all about the PyPI and I assume that you have created accounts on both of these sites. Lets start using it to share Python package on PyPI:\r\n<h3>Step 1. Create .pypirc file</h3>\r\nPlease create or update(if you already have) .pypirc file in your Home folder with the following content. This file contains the authenitication information for both PyPI Live and Test.\r\n<pre>[distutils]\r\nindex-servers =\r\n  pypi\r\n  pypitest\r\n\r\n[pypi]\r\nrepository=https://pypi.python.org/pypi\r\nusername=your_username\r\npassword=your_password\r\n\r\n[pypitest]\r\nrepository=https://testpypi.python.org/pypi\r\nusername=your_username\r\npassword=your_password\r\n</pre>\r\n<h3>Step 2. Prepare package to upload</h3>\r\nIn one of my previous post, I have added all the information to <a href=\"http://trickntip.com/write-a-python-module/\">write a Python module</a>, here I am taking the same example of setup.py file. Please note the following content in setup.py file. This is the meta data regarding your package so that any one can search your package easily using these information, therefore please make this information relative to your package.\r\n<pre>from distutils.core import setup\r\nsetup(\r\n    name = \'arithmetic\',\r\n    version = \'1.0.0\',\r\n    py_modules = [\'arithmetic\'],\r\n    author = \'trickntip.com\',\r\n    author_email = \'trickntip.com@email.com\',\r\n    url = \'http://www.trickntip.com\',\r\n    description = \'This is simple module to perform arithmetic operations.\',\r\n)\r\n</pre>\r\n<h3>Step 3. Register Package</h3>\r\nFinally you just need to register your package on PyPI Live repository. Go into your package directory and run the following command:\r\n<pre>python setup.py register -r pypi</pre>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_303\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"722\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-303\" src=\"http://trickntip.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/register-python-package-in-pypi.png\" alt=\"register-python-package-in-pypi\" width=\"722\" height=\"110\" /> Register python package in pypi[/caption]\r\n\r\n<b>Important: One thing to note here that your package must have a unique name then other packages uploaded on PyPI. If someone has already uploaded the package with the same name then you will see the following error:\r\nServer response (403): You are not allowed to store \'arithmetic\' package information\r\n</b>\r\n<h2>Summary</h2>\r\nNow you have successfully share Python package on PyPI. You can test this using pip install arithmetic. PyPI is awesome repository, that provides other simple steps to upload the package like:\r\n\r\n1. Use <a href=\"https://github.com/pypa/twine\">twine</a>\r\n2. Use the setup.py \"<a href=\"https://packaging.python.org/en/latest/distributing.html#uploading-your-project-to-pypi\">register</a>\" command.\r\n3. Or upload your PKG-INFO file (generated by distutils)\r\n\r\nIn this article, I have just described the second method.', 'Share Python Package on PyPI', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'share-python-package-pypi', '', '\nhttp://trickntip.com/write-a-python-module/', '2017-02-10 18:01:17', '2017-02-10 12:31:17', '', 0, 'http://trickntip.com/?p=301', 0, 'post', '', 1),
