ing error:\r\nServer response (403): You are not allowed to store \'arithmetic\' package information\r\n</b>\r\n<h2>Summary</h2>\r\nNow you have successfully share Python package on PyPI. You can test this using pip install arithmetic. PyPI is awesome repository, that provides other simple steps to upload the package like:\r\n\r\n1. Use <a href=\"https://github.com/pypa/twine\">twine</a>\r\n2. Use the setup.py \"<a href=\"https://packaging.python.org/en/latest/distributing.html#uploading-your-project-to-pypi\">register</a>\" command.\r\n3. Or upload your PKG-INFO file (generated by distutils)\r\n\r\nIn this article, I have just described the second method.', 'Share Python Package on PyPI', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '301-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-02-10 18:01:17', '2017-02-10 12:31:17', '', 301, 'http://trickntip.com/301-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
