(312, 1, '2017-02-24 12:44:17', '2017-02-24 07:14:17', '\r\n<p>Nowadays, .htaccess file is very important for every website. All are we know .htaccess file by SEO(Search Engine Optimization) friendly URLs because this is the main purpose that we use .htaccess file but besides this, there are many other uses of htaccess file like set cache params, server authentication, deny visitors by IP address, deny visitors by referrer, disable folder listing, Enable CGI outside of the cgi-bin and much more. Before you start using .htaccess file, it must be enabled on server.</p>\r\n<h2>.htaccess File Introduction</h2>\r\nFew days ago, we have faced an isssue with htaccess file and spent around two days. Therefore, we have decided to provide few guidelines to make .htaccess file working on Apache server.\r\n<h3>Make .htaccess working on Apache EC2</h3>\r\nMost of developers, prefer EC2 for better performace and more over Amazon provides you one year free tire that you can use to host your website. For this you have to setup Apache, MYSQL, PHP and few other packages according to your requirement. Below we have described few steps that you can follow to make .htaccess file working on EC2.\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Open file using vim or nano\r\n<pre>sudo vim /etc/apache2/apache2.conf</pre>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>Now find the line where there is\r\n<pre>             \r\n       &lt;Directory /var/www/&gt;\r\n        Options Indexes FollowSymLinks\r\n        AllowOverride None\r\n        Require all granted\r\n        &lt;/Directory&gt;\r\n\r\n</pre>\r\nreplace \"None\" with \"All\"\r\nAllowOverride All</li>\r\n 	<li>sudo a2enmod rewrite</li>\r\n 	<li>service apache2 restart</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nNow your .htaccess file must run on server. There are many tools on google that you can use to test whether your .htaccess file is working or not. Please let us know if you face any other issue and keep sharing experience. Thanks!', 'Make .htaccess working', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'make-htaccess-working', '', '', '2017-11-16 16:54:45', '2017-11-16 11:24:45', '', 0, 'http://trickntip.com/?p=312', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(313, 1, '2017-02-24 12:44:17', '2017-02-24 07:14:17', '<h2>.htaccess File Introduction</h2>\r\nNowadays, .htaccess file is very important for every website. All are we know .htaccess file by SEO(Search Engine Optimization) friendly URLs because this is the main purpose that we use .htaccess file but besides this, there are many other uses of htaccess file like set cache params, server authentication, deny visitors by IP address, deny visitors by referrer, disable folder listing, Enable CGI outside of the cgi-bin and much more. Before you start using .htaccess file, it must be enabled on server.\r\n\r\nFew days ago, we have faced an isssue with htaccess file and spent around two days. Therefore, we have decided to provide few guidelines to make .htaccess file working on Apache server.\r\n<h3>Make .htaccess working on Apache EC2</h3>\r\nMost of developers, prefer EC2 for better performace and more over Amazon provides you one year free tire that you can use to host your website. For this you have to setup Apache, MYSQL, PHP and few other packages according to your requirement. Below we have described few steps that you can follow to make .htaccess file working on EC2.\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Open file using vim or nano\r\n<pre>sudo vim /etc/apache2/apache2.conf</pre>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>Now find the line where there is\r\n<pre>             \r\n       &lt;Directory /var/www/&gt;\r\n        Options Indexes FollowSymLinks\r\n        AllowOverride None\r\n        Require all granted\r\n        &lt;/Directory&gt;\r\n\r\n</pre>\r\nreplace \"None\" with \"All\"\r\nAllowOverride All</li>\r\n 	<li>sudo a2enmod rewrite</li>\r\n 	<li>service apache2 restart</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nNow your .htaccess file must run on server. There are many tools on google that you can use to test whether your .htaccess file is working or not. Please let us know if you face any other issue and keep sharing experience. Thanks!', 'Make .htaccess working', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '312-revision-v1', '