(337, 1, '2017-11-16 12:09:31', '2017-11-16 06:39:31', 'I was just play around with Python user input to make few exercise programs for beginners. I have so many ideas to make the learning python more  interesting. Therefore, I have started about creating better program exercises so that users will take keen interest. All my programs are based on the user input from the keyboard. Input from the Keyboard in Python 3 is much similar to Python 2 but the difference is raw_input() function is renamed to input() only. \r\n<h2>Introduction to input() Function</h2>\r\ninput() function is used to take the user input from the keyboard. You can prompt the user to enter something with meaningfull message. Everything entered using input() function is of type <class \'str\'>. You need to use type casting methods to change the input and perform your operations on it.\r\n<h2>Use Case</h2>\r\n<b>Guessing Game</b> is very interesting and fits best to see the use of input() function. Well, this is a game where we generate random number between specified range and ask used to guess that number. Number range in this game can be any, generally you can generate random number between 0 - 9. Looks interesting? I\'m sure, Yes. Let\'s start making a program for this.\r\n\r\n[python]\r\nimport random\r\n\r\nrandom_number = random.randint(0,9)\r\n\r\nguess = 0\r\n\r\nprint(&quot;This is very interesting game. My program has generated a randrom number between 0 - 9 and you just need to guess that number&quot;)\r\nprint(&quot;You can type \'exit\' to quit this game&quot;)\r\ntries = 0\r\nwhile guess != random_number:\r\n\r\n    guess = input(\'What did you guess: \')\r\n\r\n    if guess == \'exit\':\r\n        break\r\n\r\n    guess = int(guess)\r\n\r\n    tries += 1\r\n    if guess &lt; random_number:\r\n        print(\'Sorry! very low\')\r\n    elif guess &gt; random_number:\r\n        print(\'Sorry! very high\')\r\n    else:\r\n        print(\'Congratulations! You got it in just \' + str(tries) + \' attempts\')\r\n[/python]\r\n<h3>Extras</h3>\r\n<p> 1. I have used one more variable \'tries\' to count the attempts that user have taken to guess the number.</p>\r\n<p> 2. You can make it more exiting to limit the number of attempts like user can only guess the number 4 times. Then you need to check the \'tries\' variable and break the program.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Summary</h2>\r\n<p>I hope you will find this program very interesting. Please leave your questions in the comment. </p>\r\n', 'Input From The Keyboard in Python 3', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'input-from-the-keyboard-in-python-3', '', '', '2017-11-16 12:14:22', '2017-11-16 06:44:22', '', 0, 'http://trickntip.com/?p=337', 0, 'post', '', 2),
