(343, 1, '2017-11-16 16:29:36', '2017-11-16 10:59:36', 'CodeIgniter 3 has introduced many features to ease the developers for faster development of web applications. All web developers love to work in CI for small web applications. It is more faster then Cake PHP and other frameworks. In this article, I will explain how to use file uploading pre-defined class in codeigniter 3.\r\n<h2>File Upload Mechanism</h2>\r\nUnderstand file upload mechanism is very easy. This process has three general steps:\r\n1. File upload form that is used to get the file from the system and send the multipart form data to the server\r\n2. Server side validations to check the valid file type. It is very important because you need to make sure that nobody can upload any malicious code or script.\r\n3. Send feedback to the client/user that file is uploaded or there is any error.\r\n\r\nThe following image will clear this more:\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-344\" src=\"http://trickntip.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/CI-file-upload.jpeg\" alt=\"ci-file-upload\" width=\"740\" height=\"357\" />\r\n<h2>Create form</h2>\r\nHere, you need to take care that you need to create a form to send multipart form data. Therefore, use form_open_multipart() function instead of form_open(). This function will automatically add enctype=\"multipart/form-data\" to form.\r\n\r\n[html]\r\n	&lt;html&gt;\r\n	&lt;head&gt;\r\n	&lt;title&gt;Upload Resume&lt;/title&gt;\r\n	&lt;/head&gt;\r\n	&lt;body&gt;\r\n\r\n	&lt;?php echo $error;?&gt;\r\n\r\n	&lt;?php echo form_open_multipart(\'user/upload_resume\');?&gt;\r\n\r\n	&lt;input type=&quot;file&quot; name=&quot;resume&quot; size=&quot;20&quot; /&gt;\r\n\r\n	\r\n\r\n\r\n	&lt;input type=&quot;submit&quot; value=&quot;upload&quot; /&gt;\r\n\r\n	&lt;/form&gt;\r\n\r\n\r\n	&lt;/body&gt;\r\n	&lt;/html&gt;\r\n[/html]\r\n\r\n<h2>Action Controller</h2>\r\nNow you need to create a controller with name User.php in your <b>application/controllers/</b> directory.\r\n\r\n[php]\r\n&lt;?php class User extends CI_Controller { \r\n        public function __construct(){ \r\n                parent::__construct(); \r\n                $this-&gt;load-&gt;helper(array(\'form\', \'url\'));\r\n	}\r\n	public function index(){\r\n		$this-&gt;load-&gt;view(\'upload_resume\', array(\'error\' =&gt; \' \' ));\r\n	}\r\n	public function upload_resume(){\r\n		//define configs\r\n		$config[\'upload_path\']          = \'./uploads/\';\r\n		$config[\'allowed_types\']        = \'doc|pdf\';\r\n		\r\n		//initialize library class\r\n		$this-&gt;load-&gt;library(\'upload\', $config);\r\n\r\n		if ( ! $this-&gt;upload-&gt;do_upload(\'resume\'))\r\n		{\r\n				$error = array(\'error\' =&gt; $this-&gt;upload-&gt;display_errors());\r\n\r\n				$this-&gt;load-&gt;view(\'upload_form\', $error);\r\n		}\r\n		else\r\n		{\r\n				$data = array(\'upload_data\' =&gt; $this-&gt;upload-&gt;data());\r\n\r\n				$this-&gt;load-&gt;view(\'upload_success\', $data);\r\n		}\r\n	}\r\n}\r\n?&gt;\r\n[/php]\r\n\r\n<h2>Show Success/Error</h2>\r\n<p>Code written from line 14 to 25 is to show the error message or load the few to show that resume has been uploaded successfully.</p>\r\n<h3>Extras</h3>\r\n1. Please make sure that you have given the right permissions to <b>uploads</b> directory.\r\n2. Handle resubmit form data on page refresh carefully to avoid submitting same file multiple times.\r\n<h2>Reference</h2>\r\nI hope you will find this article very interesting. Please leave your questions in the comment or you can check out the documentation at <a href=\"https://www.codeigniter.com/userguide3/libraries/file_uploading.html\" target=\"__blank\">File Uploading Class</a>', 'File Uploading Class in CodeIgniter 3', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'file-uploading-class-codeigniter-3', '', '', '2017-11-16 16:35:55', '2017-11-16 11:05:55', '', 0, 'http://trickntip.com/?p=343', 0, 'post', '', 0),
