with the cost. Thirdly, there is a hybrid hosting to reduce the cost. Finally, there is a cloud hosting where a customer rents a virtual server instances on-demand and frequently paid hourly basis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Several companies now offering these services like Amazon offers number of cloud hosting products in the marketplace. Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud (Amazon EC2) is a web service that provides secure, resizable compute capacity in the cloud. It is designed to make web-scale cloud computing easier for developers. EC2 can launched in minutes using an Amazon machine image.</p>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://trickntip.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/amazon.com_web_services.png\" alt=\"SaaS  IaaS PaaS amazon-com_web_services\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-362\" />\r\n\r\n<h3>IaaS Pros & Cons</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li class=\"text-success\">Reduce application launch time.</li>\r\n 	<li class=\"text-success\">Easy to shift on other cloud hosting.</li>\r\n 	<li class=\"text-success\">Easy backups and configurations.</li>\r\n 	<li class=\"text-danger\">Security issues.</li>\r\n 	<li class=\"text-danger\">Network and service delays.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Summary</h2>\r\n<p>Anybody wants to understand the cloud computing then they must have grip on cloud computing fundamentals. If you have any question please leave that in the comments below. Thanks!</p>\r\n', 'What is SaaS PaaS IaaS with Examples', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '356-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-11-23 13:26:25', '2017-11-23 07:56:25', '', 356, 'http://trickntip.com/356-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(365, 1, '2017-11-24 09:42:06', '2017-11-24 04:12:06', 'Everybody knows that SaaS, PaaS and IaaS acronyms are used for <b>Software as a Service</b>, <b>Platform as a Service</b> and <b>Infrastructure as a Service</b> respectively. These are three basic building blocks or delivery models of <b>Cloud Computing</b>. Cloud Computing is where software applications, data storage and processing capacity are accessed over the internet. It enables companies or users to consume compute resources.\r\n\r\nThere are three ways to cloud computing:\r\n<h2>Software as a Service</h2>\r\nSaaS is the easiest way to cloud computing. It allows users to run off the shelf online applications and eliminates the need for organizations to install and run applications on their own computers or in their own data centers. Hence, hardware acquisition, provisioning and maintenance expenses are almost none, as well as software licensing, installation and support.\r\n\r\nMany Google apps like google drive, google docs , google sheets and google slides are perfect examples of SaaS applications. Salesforce.com and Microsoft office 360 are also online SaaS applications.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-359\" src=\"http://trickntip.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/GoogleApps.jpg\" alt=\"SaaS IaaS PaaS\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" />\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-358\" src=\"http://trickntip.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/office365.png\" alt=\"SaaS IaaS PaaS office365\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" />\r\n<h3>SaaS Pros &amp; Cons</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li class=\"text-success\">Free or paid via subscription basis.</li>\r\n 	<li class=\"text-success\">Accessible from any computer and no need to commute.</li>\r\n 	<li class=\"text-success\">Collaborative working facility.</li>\r\n 	<li class=\"text-danger\">Generic applications not always suitable for all business models.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Platform as a Service</h2>\r\nPaaS is another cloud computing model in which a third-party provider delivers environment or a set of tools that allow users to develop their own applications over the internet. A PaaS provider hosts the hardware and software on its own infrastructure.\r\n\r\nMany companies like Microsoft has a PaaS offering Azure that allow users to develop and run windows applications in Microsoft\'s region of the cloud.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-360\" src=\"http://trickntip.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/Microsoft-Azure.png\" alt=\"SaaS IaaS PaaS microsoft-azure\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" />\r\n\r\nHeroku is another PaaS that enables developers to build, run, and operate applications entirely in the cloud. You can deploy code written in Node, Ruby, Java, PHP, Python, Go, Scala, or Clojure or use a custom buildpack to deploy apps in another language you choose.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-361\" src=\"http://trickntip.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/heroku.png\" alt=\"SaaS IaaS PaaS heroku\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" />\r\n<h3>PaaS Pros &amp; Cons</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li class=\"text-success\">Rapid application development at low cost.</li>\r\n 	<li class=\"text-success\">Private or public deployment.</li>\r\n 	<li class=\"text-danger\">Limits developers to the programming languages and other tools.</li>\r\n 	<li class=\"text-danger\">Risk of vendor lock-in as application is developed on one providers platform and difficult to move on another .</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Infrastructure as a Service</h2>\r\nIaaS allows a business to run whatever applications it requires on a supplier\'s cloud hardware. This means that existing applications can be migrated from a company data center in order to reduce IT costs. The fundamental unit of cloud infrastructure is a server. Server can be physical or virtual. Physical servers are more costly and dedicated to only one customer. Secondly, there is a dedicated hosting where a customer rents physical servers on-demand with the cost. Thirdly, there is a hybrid hosting to reduce the cost. Finally, there is a cloud hosting where a customer rents a virtual server instances on-demand and frequently paid hourly basis.\r\n\r\nSeveral companies now offering these services like Amazon offers number of cloud hosting products in the marketplace. Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud (Amazon EC2) is a web service that provides secure, resizable compute capacity in the cloud. It is designed to make web-scale cloud computing easier for developers. EC2 can launched in minutes using an Amazon machine image.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-362\" src=\"http://trickntip.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/amazon.com_web_services.png\" alt=\"SaaS IaaS PaaS amazon-com_web_services\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" />\r\n<h3>IaaS Pros &amp; Cons</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li class=\"text-success\">Reduce application launch time.</li>\r\n 	<li class=\"text-success\">Easy to shift on other cloud hosting.</li>\r\n 	<li class=\"text-success\">Easy backups and configurations.</li>\r\n 	<li class=\"text-danger\">Security issues.</li>\r\n 	<li class=\"text-danger\">Network and service delays.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Summary</h2>\r\nAnybody wants to understand the cloud computing then they must have grip on cloud computing fundamentals. If you have any question please leave that in the comments below. Thanks!', 'What is SaaS PaaS IaaS with Examples', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '356-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-11-24 09:42:06', '2017-11-24 04:12:06', '', 356, 'http://trickntip.com/356-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(366, 1, '2017-11-24 10:21:20', '2017-11-24 04:51:20', 'List and tuple are used to store the series data. This is very important and commonly used data structure in Python. I have study and explore so many things about list and tuple and decided to write a demonstration with example to show the difference between list and typle in Python. List and tuple can be confusing for you if you are beginner becauase they both look same but there are many major differences in both data structure.\r\n<h2>Declare List and Tuple</h2>\r\n<b>List</b> is always declared using the square bracket([]), for example if you want to declare the list of prime numbers you can declare it like:\r\n\r\n[python]#example of list\r\n		prime_numbers = [2, 3, 5, 7, 11, 13, 17]\r\n		print(&quot;Type of prime_number: &quot;, type(prime_numbers)) #Output: Type of prime_number:  &lt;class \'list\'&gt;[/python]\r\n\r\nNow our list of prime_numbers is stored in memory and ready for operations.\r\n\r\nGenerally, it is said that <b>Tuple</b> is declared using the parenthesis but it is really not like that. You can even declare a tuple without using parenthesis like:\r\n\r\n[python]\r\n		#example of tuple\r\n		even_numbers = 2, 4, 6, 8, 10, 12, 14\r\n		print(&quot;Type of even_numbers: &quot;, type(even_numbers)) #Output: Type of even_numbers:  &lt;class \'tuple\'&gt;\r\n		#OR\r\n		odd_numbers = (1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 11, 13)\r\n		print(&quot;Type of odd_numbers: &quot;, type(odd_numbers)) #Output: Type of odd_numbers:  &lt;class \'tuple\'&gt;\r\n	[/python]\r\n\r\nPython interpreter consider both these declarations same. You can iterate each element of list or tuple using for loop:\r\n\r\n[python]\r\n		# Loop over prime_numbers\r\n		print(&quot;List of prime numbers:&quot;)\r\n		for prime_num in prime_numbers:\r\n			print(prime_num)\r\n\r\n		# Loop over even_numbers\r\n		print(&quot;List of even numbers:&quot;)\r\n		for even_num in even_numbers:\r\n			print(even_num);\r\n\r\n		# Loop over odd_numbers\r\n		print(&quot;List of odd numbers:&quot;)\r\n		for odd_num in odd_numbers:\r\n			print(odd_num);\r\n	[/python]\r\n\r\nLists and tuples are working similar so far only the difference is syntax. But guys it is really not like that. There are mainly 3 notable differences in List and Tuple:\r\n<h3>1. List occupy more memory than tuples</h3>\r\nYou need to be very carefull before you start declare the sequences like list. List takes more space in momory then tuples. List has more methods than tuples. Lets see the following example:\r\n\r\n[python]\r\n		print(&quot;List Methods:&quot;)\r\n		print(dir(prime_numbers))\r\n		print(&quot;-&quot;*80);\r\n\r\n		print(\'Tuple Methods:\')\r\n		print(dir(even_numbers))\r\n	[/python]\r\n\r\nSee the output:\r\n<pre>	List Methods:\r\n	[\'__add__\', \'__class__\', \'__contains__\', \'__delattr__\', \'__delitem__\', \'__dir__\', \'__doc__\', \'__eq__\', \'__format__\', \'__ge__\', \'__getattribute__\', \'__getitem__\', \'__gt__\', \'__hash__\', \'__iadd__\', \'__imul__\', \'__init__\', \'__iter__\', \'__le__\', \'__len__\', \'__lt__\', \'__mul__\', \'__ne__\', \'__new__\', \'__reduce__\', \'__reduce_ex__\', \'__repr__\', \'__reversed__\', \'__rmul__\', \'__setattr__\', \'__setitem__\', \'__sizeof__\', \'__str__\', \'__subclasshook__\', \'append\', \'clear\', \'copy\', \'count\', \'extend\', \'index\', \'insert\', \'pop\', \'remove\', \'reverse\', \'sort\']\r\n	--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n	Tuple Methods:\r\n	[\'__add__\', \'__class__\', \'__contains__\', \'__delattr__\', \'__dir__\', \'__doc__\', \'__eq__\', \'__format__\', \'__ge__\', \'__getattribute__\', \'__getitem__\', \'__getnewargs__\', \'__gt__\', \'__hash__\', \'__init__\', \'__iter__\', \'__le__\', \'__len__\', \'__lt__\', \'__mul__\', \'__ne__\', \'__new__\', \'__reduce__\', \'__reduce_ex__\', \'__repr__\', \'__rmul__\', \'__setattr__\', \'__sizeof__\', \'__str__\', \'__subclasshook__\', \'count\', \'index\']\r\n</pre>\r\nYou can see list has more methods then tuple. One more thing you can do, you can check the size of list and tuple variable using \'sys\' module.\r\n\r\n[python]	\r\n		import sys\r\n		list_eg = [1, 2, 3, &quot;a&quot;, &quot;b&quot;, 45.90, 12.00]\r\n		tuple_eg = (1, 2, 3, &quot;a&quot;, &quot;b&quot;, 45.90, 12.00)\r\n		print(&quot;List size: &quot;, sys.getsizeof(list_eg), &quot; Bytes&quot;)\r\n		print(&quot;Tuple size: &quot;, sys.getsizeof(tuple_eg), &quot; Bytes&quot;)\r\n	[/python]\r\n\r\nYou will notice that list size is larger in bytes than tuple size.\r\n<pre>	List size:  120  Bytes\r\n	Tuple size:  104  Bytes\r\n</pre>\r\n<h3>2. Mutability Vs Immutability</h3>\r\n<b>Tuples</b> can not be changed once declared so they are immutable but lists can be altered so they are mutable. If you will take a deep look at first point where we listed the list methods, you see list has append, insert, pop and remove methods but tuple does not have. Lets see the following example:\r\n\r\n[python]\r\n	list_eg = [1, 2, 3, &quot;a&quot;, &quot;b&quot;, 45.90, 12.00]\r\n	tuple_eg = (1, 2, 3, &quot;a&quot;, &quot;b&quot;, 45.90, 12.00)\r\n	list_eg.append(\'True\')\r\n	print(list_eg)\r\n	tuple_eg.append(\'False\') \r\n[/python]\r\n\r\nThe last line will throw the \'AttributeError: \'tuple\' object has no attribute \'append\'\' error. A tuple can not be changed once created. Only declare your sequence a list if you want to modify throughout your program otherwise declare it as a tuple to same memory and faster execution.\r\n<h3>3. Tuple with one element mistery</h3>\r\nThe last main thing about the tuple that is misterious too. Before we dig into this lets see the following code:\r\n\r\n[python]\r\n	empty_tuple = ()\r\n	test1 = (&quot;a&quot;)\r\n	test2 = (&quot;a&quot;,&quot;b&quot;)\r\n	test3 = (&quot;a&quot;,&quot;b&quot;,&quot;c&quot;)\r\n	print(empty_tuple)\r\n	print(test1)\r\n	print(test2)\r\n	print(test3)\r\n[/python]\r\n\r\nOutput:\r\n<pre>	()\r\n	a\r\n	(\'a\', \'b\')\r\n	(\'a\', \'b\', \'c\')\r\n</pre>\r\nEverything looks expected but not the line two. We have assigned the tuple(\"a\") to variable test1 but it looks like it has assigned the string a to test1 variable. test1 is just a string now. To create a tuple with just one element you need to do the following:\r\n\r\n[python]\r\n	test1 = (&quot;a&quot;,)\r\n	print(test1)\r\n[/python]\r\n\r\nNow test1 is a tuple. The reason of this was a tuple assignment. A tuple has a great feature to assign the value of each tuple to variables like:\r\n\r\n[python]\r\n	name, age, city = (\'Jazz\', 24,\'San Diago\')\r\n	print(&quot;Name: &quot;,name)\r\n	print(&quot;Age: &quot;,age)\r\n	print(&quot;City: &quot;,city)\r\n[/python]\r\n\r\nOutput:\r\n<pre>	Name:  Jazz\r\n	Age:  24\r\n	City:  San Diago\r\n</pre>\r\n<h2>Summary</h2>\r\nList and tuple, both are very strong feature of Python and interesting for beginners. If you have any question please leave the comment below. Thanks!', 'Difference Between List and Tuple in Python', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '353-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-11-24 10:21:20', '2017-11-24 04:51:20', '', 353, 'http://trickntip.com/353-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
