(422, 1, '2018-01-22 18:13:10', '2018-01-22 12:43:10', 'Wowza Streaming Engine Manager has a wonderful feature that is <b>Transcoder</b> to get the stream thumbnails when the stream is incoming. You must enable <b>Transcoder</b> for this and you can easily get the thumbnail using HTTP provider.\r\n\r\nYou need to make changes in <code>VHost.xml</code> file. Just add the following lines of code in the file and upload back to the server.\r\n<pre>&lt;HTTPProvider&gt;\r\n &lt;BaseClass&gt;com.wowza.wms.transcoder.httpprovider.HTTPTranscoderThumbnail&lt;/BaseClass&gt;\r\n &lt;RequestFilters&gt;transcoderthumbnail*&lt;/RequestFilters&gt;\r\n &lt;AuthenticationMethod&gt;none&lt;/AuthenticationMethod&gt;\r\n&lt;/HTTPProvider&gt;\r\n</pre>\r\nRestart Wowza Streaming Engine\r\n<pre>	service WowzaStreamingEngine restart\r\n</pre>\r\nAwesome! you are ready to get wowza live stream thumbnail. Open your browser and use the following syntax to build the URL:\r\n<pre>	http://[wowza-ip-address]:8086/transcoderthumbnail?application=[application-name]&amp;streamname=[stream-name]&amp;format=[jpeg or png]&amp;size=[widthxheight]\r\n</pre>\r\n<b>Example:</b>\r\n<pre>	http://127.112.223.114:8086/transcoderthumbnail?application=live&amp;streamname=myStream&amp;format=jpeg&amp;size=1600x1600\r\n</pre>\r\nYou can use <b>GoCoder</b> App to send the stream with the name <b>myStream</b> and hit the URL again.\r\n\r\n<b>IMPORTANT: There must be an incoming stream to get the thumbnail. The Video-On-Demand(VOD) will not work in this. <b>Transcoder</b> only works on the live streams.</b>\r\n\r\nPlease see a video for the same:\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/-x-7Ycrl2Uw\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe>\r\n\r\nPlease leave questions in the comment below. Thanks!', 'Wowza Live Stream thumbnail', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'wowza-live-stream-thumbnail', '', '', '2018-01-22 18:13:10', '2018-01-22 12:43:10', '', 0, 'http://trickntip.com/?p=422', 0, 'post', '', 0),
